        <h2> Arts & Culture</h2>
        <p>
          - <strong>Padma Awards (India)</strong>: Padma Shri, Padma Bhushan, and Padma Vibhushan honor Indian citizens for distinguished contributions in arts, literature, and public service.<br/>
          - <strong>Bharat Ratna</strong>: India's highest civilian award, also awarded for exceptional service in art and culture.<br/>
          - <strong>Academy Awards (Oscars)</strong>: International recognition for excellence in film, awarded by the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2> Science & Technology</h2>
        <p>
          - <strong>Nobel Prize in Physics/Chemistry/Medicine</strong>: Prestigious global awards recognizing groundbreaking discoveries.<br/>
          - <strong>Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize</strong>: India's top science award for outstanding research across multiple disciplines.<br/>
          - <strong>Infosys Prize</strong>: Recognizes Indian researchers for impactful contributions in science, mathematics, engineering, and social sciences.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2> Literature</h2>
        <p>
          - <strong>Sahitya Akademi Award</strong>: Given annually to writers for outstanding books in Indian languages.<br/>
          - <strong>Jnanpith Award</strong>: Highest literary honor in India for lifelong contribution to literature.<br/>
          - <strong>Nobel Prize in Literature</strong>: Internationally awarded to authors for excellence in literary work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2> Sports</h2>
        <p>
          - <strong>Major Dhyan Chand Khel Ratna</strong>: India's highest sporting honor.<br/>
          - <strong>Arjuna Award</strong>: For consistent outstanding performance in sports.<br/>
          - <strong>Laureus World Sports Awards</strong>: Recognizes international athletes and teams for exceptional performances.
        </p>
      </section>

